history.content: That is likely. My understanding is that you would be placed in the front of the waitlist and if there was space in your new section (including students enrolled via both 186 and 286A), would be likely to be processed into the class at the next automatic waitlist processing.  (If students have had other experiences, please share -- student reports are how we've learned ~ 30% of what we know about how the system works since campus documentation is uneven.)

If I am currently enrolled in a class that has also has a graduate version in the same room (specifically, 186/286A), will using Options to swap to an open section result in losing my place, seeing as many undergraduates are still waitlisted?
history.subject: Changing sections
